The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 US firm to offer mobile messages

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, March 28: Mobile 365, a US-based mobile messaging and data services company, has entered India and set a target of delivering 20 million messages a month over the next one year.

 Mobile 365 operates in 18 countries around the world and facilitates the delivery of over 2 billion mobile messages a month.

 The Indian mobile market is growing at a fast pace and offers exciting opportunities for domestic mobile operators looking to monetise content, as well as international content companies seeking expansion in growth markets, said Matthew Talbot, managing director (Asia) of Mobile 365.

 The company will engage with local operators, portals, and TV broadcasters to offer advanced mobile solutions and deliver messages, said Kaustuv Ghosh, country manager (India) of Mobile 365. 




